Are you guys kidding do you read his story…he downloaded it fresh and compiled it when he got it…hint hint the problem is probly an anti-leach. i’m just saying since the only time i get the 100 error code is when I left out a “}” or a important piece of code, so I’m going to say its probly has an anit-leech
[/quote]
Are YOU kidding me? Read the errors. the “100 error code” you’re talking about is when you miss a line in a single file, so all 100 errors are in that single file. His “100 error code” (Note: The java compiler only shows, at max, 100 errors) is for every single file he has, more specifically every declaration of signlink. Again, he needs to add: package sign; at the top of his signlink.java[/quote]
Sorry but after reading his story its the only reason I can think of, but you could be right since the 100 errors never shows, not for me, the starting error
